name: QUILEUTE TRIBAL NATION
sampleDescriptions: General tribal representation, including natural resource protection.
Issues related to federal Indian policy, including Tribal governance, sovereignty, and general representation before federal agencies.
Monitoring federal policies and administrative actions related to natural resource management, fisheries, marine resources, and environmental protection affecting Tribal lands and treaty resources.
Monitoring federal education policy and Bureau of Indian Education matters, including issues related to Tribal school facilities and education infrastructure.
